b'[<p><i><b>UFC Fight Night: Belfort vs. Henderson 2</b></i> (also known as <i><b>UFC Fight Night 32</b></i>) was a <a href="/wiki/Mixed_martial_arts" title="Mixed martial arts">mixed martial arts</a> event held on November 9, 2013, at the <a href="/wiki/Goi%C3%A2nia_Arena" title="Goi\xc3\xa2nia Arena">Goi\xc3\xa2nia Arena</a> in <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Goi%C3%A2nia,_Brazil" title="Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil">Goi\xc3\xa2nia, Brazil</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup> The event was broadcast live on <a href="/wiki/Fox_Sports_1" title="Fox Sports 1">Fox Sports 1</a>.\n</p>, <p>The event was headlined by a rematch between longtime multi-divisional contenders <a href="/wiki/Vitor_Belfort" title="Vitor Belfort">Vitor Belfort</a> and <a href="/wiki/Dan_Henderson" title="Dan Henderson">Dan Henderson</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-UFCFN32_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-UFCFN32-3">[3]</a></sup> Henderson defeated Belfort in their first encounter in 2006 at <a href="/wiki/Pride_32" title="Pride 32">Pride 32</a> in a unanimous decision.\n</p>, <p>The co-main event featured the long-awaited bout between <a href="/wiki/The_Ultimate_Fighter:_Brazil" title="The Ultimate Fighter: Brazil">The Ultimate Fighter: Brazil</a> competitors <a href="/wiki/Cezar_Ferreira" title="Cezar Ferreira">Cezar Ferreira</a> and <a href="/wiki/Daniel_Sarafian" title="Daniel Sarafian">Daniel Sarafian</a>. Both men were originally scheduled to face each other in the finale to determine the winner of the inaugural TUF series for Brazil. However, Sarafian injured himself before the finale in June 2012 and was forced out of the finals.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Thiago_Tavares" title="Thiago Tavares">Thiago Tavares</a> was expected to face <a href="/wiki/Quinn_Mulhern" title="Quinn Mulhern">Quinn Mulhern</a> at the event. However, Mulhern pulled out of the bout citing an injury and was replaced by <a href="/wiki/Justin_Salas" title="Justin Salas">Justin Salas</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-MulhernOut_5-0"><a href="#cite_note-MulhernOut-5">[5]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p><a href="/wiki/Johnny_Eduardo" title="Johnny Eduardo">Johnny Eduardo</a> and <a href="/wiki/Lucas_Martins" title="Lucas Martins">Lucas Martins</a> were originally scheduled to face each other in a bantamweight bout on this card. However, both fighters were injured and the fight was removed from the event.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup>\n</p>, <p>The following fighters were awarded $50,000 bonuses.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-8"><a href="#cite_note-8">[7]</a></sup>\n</p>]'